1
00:00:58,360 --> 00:00:58,840
Get out.

2
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:00,360
Leave.

3
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:11,560
Sir,

4
00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:13,480
here's the wine you ordered.

5
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:16,800
Stop.

6
00:01:19,039 --> 00:01:19,760
Wow.

7
00:01:20,600 --> 00:01:22,400
How come you look so much like me?

8
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:22,880
Sir,

9
00:01:23,160 --> 00:01:25,220
looking alike is just a coincidence.

10
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:26,120
Wait.

11
00:01:27,120 --> 00:01:28,120
What is your name?

12
00:01:28,480 --> 00:01:29,340
I'm sorry, sir.

13
00:01:29,480 --> 00:01:31,560
We don't disclose personal information.

14
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:33,690
Are you my father's illegitimate son?

15
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:35,280
Sir,

16
00:01:35,520 --> 00:01:37,320
if there's nothing else, I'll take my leave.

17
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:37,880
Come.

18
00:01:38,360 --> 00:01:40,160
Have a couple more drinks with me.

19
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:40,880
Sorry, sir.

20
00:01:41,240 --> 00:01:43,440
We cannot provide this kind of service.

21
00:01:55,560 --> 00:01:56,759
They look so similar.

22
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:58,520
Damn.

23
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,300
Who is paying for tonight?

24
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:07,540
Mr. Ding is paying.

25
00:02:15,920 --> 00:02:16,450
Ding Wen.

26
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:18,320
What are you doing here?

27
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:18,960
Brothers,

28
00:02:19,440 --> 00:02:20,800
this private room is nice.

29
00:02:20,800 --> 00:02:22,200
Let's sing here tonight.

30
00:02:22,200 --> 00:02:23,200
Okay, bro.

31
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:25,560
You, get out.

32
00:02:26,120 --> 00:02:26,680
Why?

33
00:02:30,560 --> 00:02:31,600
Why?

34
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:34,520
Because my driving skills are better than yours.

35
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,160
Gu Haoran.

36
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:38,000
You've been racing for so many years,

37
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,880
and your skills are still like this.

38
00:02:39,880 --> 00:02:41,320
Have you no shame?

39
00:02:42,120 --> 00:02:42,650
Ding Wen.

40
00:02:43,240 --> 00:02:44,570
Who do you think you are?

41
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,000
How dare you laugh at me?

42
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,060
You are not worthy.

43
00:02:47,240 --> 00:02:48,440
Still not convinced?

44
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:50,600
That's good.

45
00:02:51,240 --> 00:02:53,440
The Wutong Mountain Track is right next door.

46
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:54,900
Do you dare to race with me?

47
00:02:55,320 --> 00:02:56,040
Of course.

48
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:57,160
The loser

49
00:02:57,440 --> 00:02:59,170
has to give up this private room

50
00:02:59,560 --> 00:03:01,200
and roll out of here.

51
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:02,720
Remember,

52
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,080
you have to roll.

53
00:03:06,360 --> 00:03:06,800
Okay.

54
00:03:07,840 --> 00:03:08,840
Get ready to roll.

55
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,760
Let's go race.

56
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:18,960
Loser.

57
00:03:19,640 --> 00:03:21,570
It's still not too late to back out.

58
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,370
Cut the crap.

59
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,360
When you're rolling on the ground later,

60
00:03:24,360 --> 00:03:25,960
make sure to watch your hair.

61
00:03:27,640 --> 00:03:28,170
Alright.

62
00:03:28,880 --> 00:03:30,480
See you at the starting line.

63
00:03:32,480 --> 00:03:34,810
Let's go. We'll wait at the starting line.

64
00:03:48,720 --> 00:03:49,160
Sir.

65
00:03:52,440 --> 00:03:53,720
I don't have time to drink with you right now.

66
00:03:53,720 --> 00:03:55,320
I have business to attend to.

67
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:31,440
Sir,

68
00:04:31,840 --> 00:04:33,240
I suggest you don't race.

69
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,409
What do you mean?

70
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,760
You are bound to lose this race.

71
00:04:43,440 --> 00:04:45,240
My Audi R8

72
00:04:45,520 --> 00:04:46,920
is a 640-horsepower V10

73
00:04:47,159 --> 00:04:50,220
equipped with the ALA 2.0 active aerodynamics system.

74
00:04:50,800 --> 00:04:52,240
The ALA system of the Audi R8

75
00:04:52,240 --> 00:04:53,000
in continuous S-curves

76
00:04:53,000 --> 00:04:54,760
doesn't have time to switch to downforce mode.

77
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:55,680
The wind speed changes on mountain roads

78
00:04:55,680 --> 00:04:57,810
will also affect its airflow sensors.

79
00:05:03,800 --> 00:05:05,120
Okay, then tell me,

80
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:08,040
what is the advantage of that kid's broken car?

81
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:09,520
That gentleman,

82
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,680
his GTR R34

83
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:11,720
is the same model as

84
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:13,240
Paul Walker's in Fast & Furious.

85
00:05:13,240 --> 00:05:14,440
Its rear-wheel steering system

86
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,400
can reduce understeer

87
00:05:15,400 --> 00:05:16,960
by 27 percent on hairpin turns.

88
00:05:16,960 --> 00:05:18,640
Not to mention its RWS chassis,

89
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,720
which, on bumpy roads,

90
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:22,240
gives the tires 0.3 seconds more contact time.

91
00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:23,970
On these continuous S-curves,

92
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:25,400
you can't beat him at all.

93
00:05:30,040 --> 00:05:32,100
Well, my car is 50 kilograms lighter.

94
00:05:32,440 --> 00:05:34,170
It's light in the wrong places.

95
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,720
All your weight reduction is concentrated in the lower half of the car.

96
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:39,280
The center of gravity is as high as walking on stilts.

97
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,840
I just looked at your tire temperature gauge.

98
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,360
The current surface temperature is 19 degrees.

99
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,920
Your Pirelli P Zero Corsa tires

100
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,760
need to reach 40 degrees to get grip.

101
00:05:45,760 --> 00:05:46,800
If you hit a slippery road,

102
00:05:46,800 --> 00:05:47,760
the slip ratio of your front left wheel

103
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,090
will exceed 47 percent.

104
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:53,900
Cut the crap. I'm leaving.

105
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:57,560
Get out of the way.

106
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,840
Seal off the mountain road.

107
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:19,920
The race has officially started.

108
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:35,640
Both cars are very fast.

109
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,920
But for cars on mountain roads,

110
00:06:36,920 --> 00:06:39,760
the downforce of the GTR34 seems more stable.

111
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:51,040
Sure enough, the GTR34 overtakes the R8 entering the first corner.

112
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,880
Both sides are setting new speeds.

113
00:06:52,880 --> 00:06:54,520
The R8 refuses to yield.

114
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,650
It accelerates past the GTR34 through the third corner.

115
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:06,240
They are neck and neck with no clear winner.

116
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,440
The GTR34 is applying intense pressure.

117
00:07:13,440 --> 00:07:16,170
The R8 is feeling the gap in vehicle performance.

118
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:05,650
The R8 has lost its cool and is actually accelerating in the corner.

119
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,280
There's an accident.

120
00:08:11,280 --> 00:08:12,480
Something happened.

121
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:17,960
Mr. Ding.

122
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:20,010
Help me get rid of Gu Haoran.

123
00:08:20,280 --> 00:08:21,010
Why should I?

124
00:08:22,000 --> 00:08:24,330
I'll give you ten million. How about that?

125
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:32,330
Mr. Ding.

126
00:08:32,720 --> 00:08:34,200
It's best if it looks like an accident.

127
00:08:34,200 --> 00:08:35,260
I get what you mean.

128
00:08:39,320 --> 00:08:40,760
How dare you compete with me.

129
00:08:40,760 --> 00:08:41,559
Go to hell!

130
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:14,140
Sister Luo.

131
00:09:23,760 --> 00:09:25,890
Buy the bar, delete the surveillance,

132
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:28,140
and keep everyone's mouths shut.

133
00:09:28,480 --> 00:09:29,410
Yes, Sister Luo.

134
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:44,440
Sorry,

135
00:09:44,560 --> 00:09:45,620
we are not open yet.

136
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:55,280
Good.

137
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:56,920
Take him away.

138
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:01,340
What are you doing?

139
00:10:01,560 --> 00:10:02,000
No,

140
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,380
what are you doing?

141
00:10:17,080 --> 00:10:18,740
Chairman, the person is here.

142
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:22,740
Who are you?

143
00:10:23,160 --> 00:10:24,090
What do you want?

144
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,480
My name is Gu Zhenhong,

145
00:10:26,960 --> 00:10:28,760
the chairman of Gu Group.

146
00:10:29,120 --> 00:10:29,840
I'm sorry

147
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,200
for bringing you here this way.

148
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,160
Gu Group?

149
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,680
What does that have to do with me?

150
00:10:34,680 --> 00:10:35,400
Let me go!

151
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:39,640
This is my grandson, Gu Haoran.

152
00:10:39,960 --> 00:10:41,620
You must be familiar with him.

153
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,840
Because of a traffic accident,

154
00:10:45,600 --> 00:10:47,000
he was severely injured.

155
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,680
Gu Haoran, the new CEO of Gu Group,

156
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:51,640
is in a coma due to a car accident.

157
00:10:51,720 --> 00:10:53,920
The new energy vehicle project he led

158
00:10:54,120 --> 00:10:55,380
is facing suspension.

159
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,800
This accident caused Gu Group's stock

160
00:10:57,920 --> 00:10:59,320
to plummet by 10 billion.

161
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:09,000
As the CEO of our Gu Group, Haoran

162
00:11:09,520 --> 00:11:10,760
has fully taken over

163
00:11:10,920 --> 00:11:12,600
our family's main business.

164
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:16,160
The stock has just gone public.

165
00:11:16,680 --> 00:11:20,560
Once it is exposed that his injury left him in a vegetative state,

166
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,810
the stock price will continue to plummet.

167
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:25,400
Therefore,

168
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,720
the new energy vehicle project he led

169
00:11:27,840 --> 00:11:28,900
will fall through.

170
00:11:29,240 --> 00:11:30,120
So...

171
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:34,360
So you want me to replace him.
